body_html:
@sshrdp Soroush, I found that the problem got worse since 1.5.0.
Not even Linux python 2.7 can import boosted_trees.
I installed 1.4.1 and 1.5.0 in different virtualenv, and checked the diffs.
$ (cd tf-1.4/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/contrib/boosted_trees/estimator_batch && ls *.py)
custom_export_strategy.py custom_loss_head.py estimator.py init.py model.py trainer_hooks.py
$ (cd tf-1.5/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/contrib/boosted_trees/estimator_batch && ls *.py)
custom_export_strategy.py init.py trainer_hooks.py

Many files are taken out in tf-1.5.0, even though I cannot find significant changes regarding BUILD or init.py under boosted_trees between the two versions.

Could it be due to some BUILD file changes like this commit or another..?

body:
@sshrdp Soroush, I found that the problem got worse since 1.5.0.
Not even Linux python 2.7 can import boosted_trees.
I installed 1.4.1 and 1.5.0 in different virtualenv, and checked the diffs.
$ (cd tf-1.4/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/contrib/boosted_trees/estimator_batch && ls *.py)
custom_export_strategy.py  custom_loss_head.py  estimator.py  __init__.py  model.py  trainer_hooks.py
$ (cd tf-1.5/lib/python2.7/site-packages/tensorflow/contrib/boosted_trees/estimator_batch && ls *.py)
custom_export_strategy.py  __init__.py  trainer_hooks.py

Many files are taken out in tf-1.5.0, even though I cannot find significant changes regarding BUILD or __init__.py under boosted_trees between the two versions.

Could it be due to some BUILD file changes like [this commit](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/commit/66b1615b6e2783c9ddce27e7b084fcc230c3a594#diff-133d898664bdd5d74926bf66659adb53) or [another](https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/commit/966016b7f2382658e7c84baae0596d35f0a49bae#diff-133d898664bdd5d74926bf66659adb53)..?
